ied object is the USER, and <code>rt_author_items</code> (an ACF repeater on the user) resolves via <code>user_{id}</code>. The FRONTEND renders these rows correctly. The EDITOR row picker forwards <code>preview_type=archive/author</code> + the user id; the rows ajax must match that (not the bare <code>author</code> prefix) for the picker to enumerate. Repro: set “Preview Dynamic Content as → Author archive”, pick this site’s admin (the v8-seeded user), and open a Repeater Row tag’s row picker — it lists the two author rows when the branch matches, and comes up empty when it does not.</p>","text_color":"#374151","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"size":14,"unit":"px"}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true}],"isInner":false}]